    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1357"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1357">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/865.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Davis</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 587.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Guadalajara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 18, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: * * * The Carrancista Government has abrogated
                    the edict as to the re-collection of taxes paid to the Villistas.</p>
                <p>As, according to the mining tax law, owners have until the end of October before
                    forfeiting all rights to redeem, I am advising them to take the full time before
                    paying, which they can do with safety.</p>
                <p>If the Department can give me instructions as to how to better or further advise,
                    I would feel thankful.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Will B. Davis.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
